ProcedureHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: PROC HADOOP <hadoop-server-option(s)>; 
  HDFS <hadoop-server-option(s)> <hdfs-command-option(s)>; 
  MAPREDUCE <hadoop-server-option(s)> <mapreduce-option(s)>; 
  PIG <hadoop-server-option(s)> <pig-code-option(s)>; 
  PROPERTIES <configuration-properties>;

The HADOOP procedure enables SAS to interact with Hadoop data by running Apache Hadoop code. 
Apache Hadoop is an open-source framework, written in Java, that provides distributed data 
storage and processing of large amounts of data. 

PROC HADOOP interfaces with the Hadoop JobTracker. This is the service within Hadoop that controls 
tasks to specific nodes in the cluster. PROC HADOOP enables you to submit the following: 

  • Hadoop Distributed File System (HDFS) commands
  • MapReduce programs
  • Pig language code
